Austrolestes aridus is an Australian species of damselfly in the family Lestidae,
commonly known as an inland ringtail. 
It is widespread across inland Australia, where it inhabits streams, pools, and ponds.Austrolestes aridus is a medium-sized to large damselfly, the male is light blue and black in colour, with a pale band near the tip of his tail.Austrolestes aridus appears similar to Austrolestes analis which is found across southern Australia.